- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper discusses the computing power of DNA strand displacement structures, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper investigates the computational power of a restricted class of DNA strand displacement structures, which is related to the study of computational complexity. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the use of DNA strand displacement structures as a potential computing technology, which falls under the category of emerging technologies. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper studies signal-processing gates based on DNA strand displacement structures, which is related to the control of systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the formalization and mechanical verification of DNA strand displacement systems, which involves programming language concepts such as formalization and verification.
